Description.Name: What's in a Name?
Description.Details: Arriving at Medical Facilities to check on your mystery guest, you stroll through the doorway and approach one of the MedTechs seated at a terminal, "Hey there... MedTech Anderson," you say as you look at the Techs name badge, "Which bed did the [[SCN_MW,{SCN_MW.Callsign}]] get assigned?" The MedTech starts to give a smart-assed answer as he looks up and notices who you are, and promptly changes his tune, "Do I look like a... Umm, ohh... Commander {COMMANDER.LastName}... uhhh Let me... uhh... look that up for you sir. They are in one of the private rooms, Suite 06 to be precise, sir." You nod your thanks and head over to Hospital wing and Suite 06. A Doctor and a team of MedTechs are checking the advanced bed diagnostic panels showing the vitals of the mystery patient. Dr Swinsen notices you standing at the door to the private room, "Commander, please, come in. Nothing much has changed since they were brought in." You look at the screens, unable to make any sense of the data shown, "How long do you think they will remain in this state?" The MedTech points at their partner and responds, "Well, they are receiving the best care possible on the Argo with no expenses spared, so hopefully it will only be one to two weeks before we can safely wake them from thier comatose state."

Description.Name: switch to Basic Medical Care
Description.Details: [approximately 8 weeks recovery]

Description.Name: Basic Medical
Description.Details:
You weigh up the current costs against continuing to spend money on additional medical care before deciding to save some money on an unknown outcome, "Hate to say, but we need to keep the MedSuites available for our best active duty personel.  Move our guest to MedBay One and alert me to any changes to their condition, good or bad, clear?"

The Doctor nods and makes a note in the patient's file and they start prepping to move them to MedBay One, "Understood, Commander."

<color=#E62E00>[[SCN_MW,{SCN_MW.Callsign}]] estimated time comatose: approximately 6-8 Weeks</color>
